<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3410] split DataSourceTest into test for basic datasources and j2ee datasources</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3410</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The test DataSourceTest is currently not run with JSR169, because the test includes calls to classes and methods that are not supported in that environment.&lt;br/&gt;
However, with JSR169 the only supported connection mechanism is a datasource, so it seems very hollowing to not even have this test run with JSR169.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I posted a question, asking if a split was a good idea (with an initial attempt), in thread:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/minimized-DataSourceTest-for-JSR169--to15364534.html#a15364534&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/minimized-DataSourceTest-for-JSR169--to15364534.html#a15364534&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
